fluxus-video - video texture and capture module for fluxus
(C) 2009 Gabor Papp, http://mndl.hu/

Video module based on the video code of openFrameworks
(http://www.openframeworks.cc/).

Building and installing instructions
------------------------------------

Fluxus-video requires scons and GStreamer, unicap, ffmpeg on Linux and
Quicktime on OSX.

Before building on Linux make sure to install gstreamer-devel-0.10,
gstreamer-plugins-base-devel-0.10, gstreamer-plugins-good-devel, and
gstreamer-plugins-bad-devel, unicap-devel, ffmpeg-devel on fedora or
libunicap-dev, libgstreamer-0.10-dev, libgstreamer-plugins-base0.10-dev,
libavformat-dev, libswscale-dev, libavcodec-dev, libavutil-dev on ubuntu.


To build and install just type 'scons' and 'sudo scons install' in the main
fluxus directory and if every package requirements are met the video module is
built and installed.

